cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.GR

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision and machine learning techniques for video object segmentation, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also proposes a deep interactive image segmentation method, which involves training a neural network, and thus could also be categorized under artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The iterative refinement process used in the system could be considered a form of active learning, which is a subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the GrabCut dataset, which is a popular benchmark for image segmentation, and thus could be categorized under multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses user behavior and usage patterns, which could be categorized under graphics (cs.GR).
